recent_25_results.question: 1.7 What is the main difference between a while and a do...while statement?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 1.7 A do...while loop will always execute atleast once, a while loop may never execute depending on teh conditions.

recent_25_results.question: 1.7 What is the main difference between a while and a do...while statement?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 1.7 a while loop is pre-check (it checks the condition statement before it executes the code within the while block) a do while loop is post-check (it checks the condition AFTER the block executes, it runs at least once no matter what the condition statement is)

recent_25_results.question: 1.7 What is the main difference between a while and a do...while statement?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 1.7 )) What is the main difference between a while and a do...while statement? The do while construct consists of a block of code and a condition. The difference between the While loop is it tests the condition before the code within the block is executed.
